A New York City councilmember had his apartment building covered in graffiti after he attended a drag queen story time event for children at a local library.

Erik Bottcher was confronted by demonstrators outside the event on Saturday in Manhattan, and on Monday he said they had attacked his home - an action condemned by the mayor as 'completely outrageous'.

Bottcher shared photos of the graffiti on Twitter, saying: 'Tonight the Drag Story Hour protesters came to my apartment building and gained entry. My super called the cops and two of them were arrested for trespassing.'

On the sidewalk was written in chalk: 'Eric Bottcher is a pedo child groomer'.

The attack is just the latest in a recent spate of violent incidents involving drag queen reading events, which critics say are inappropriate for children.

General Berger Names His Replacement
By Michael Baxter -December 16, 20224833916

General David H. Berger Thursday night put a quick end to speculation over who would fill his shoes as commander of the White Hat partition of the United States military. He had summoned his councilâ€”currently 12 high-ranking officers from all branches of the armed forcesâ€”to an encrypted video call to deliver the news: His successor would be Assistant Commandant of The Marine Corps Eric M. Smith, a valiant, battle-hardened officer who had led Marines into combat in Iraq and Afghanistan.

His meritorious accolades are legendary, and Marines revere him.  Afghanistan and Iraq aside, Gen. Smith commanded U.S. Marine Corps Forces Southern Command, 1st Marine Division, III Marine Expeditionary Force, and Marine Corps Combat Development Command.

More recently, he had helped draft the battle plan that allowed a joint Special Operations task force to seize FEMAâ€™s Mount Weather stronghold.

Gen. Smith, who was absent the call, would assume command of all White Hat military operations effective January 1, Gen. Berger said, adding that heâ€™d retain authority in the interim.

â€œGeneral Smith is the right Marine for this job,â€ General Berger told the council. â€œMany of you have met him, and know his reputation. The few of you who havenâ€™t will get to know him soon enough. Heâ€™s no nonsense. A Marine and a true patriot. Heâ€™s gonna shake things up, and youâ€™ll show him the same respect and deference youâ€™ve shown me. Iâ€™ll still be around, advising from the lines. But General Smith will be quarterbacking.â€

Why China Loves Conservatives
by Eric Hendriks-Kim

"In Â­China there is a great deal of love for Western conservative authors: The works of Samuel Â­Huntington and Leo Strauss, for instance, are studied and admired by Chinese intellectuals and academics. And Chinese interpretations of American politics often parallel those of the American Right. These affinities undoubtedly have many causes, but one shared belief stands out: a profound sense that any Â­society, and a healthy one in particular, is held together by an integral, holistic culture...

The Chinese term for North Americaâ€™s identity politicsâ€”baizuo (â€œwhite Leftâ€)â€”is strongly derogatory. It implies something like â€œthe wild stuff lefty whites say these days.â€ Even scholars from Chinaâ€™s most liberal faction, such as intellectual historian Xu Jilin, judge North Americaâ€™s baizuo to be excessive and divisive... To many of a certain age, such as the dissident artist Ai Weiwei, baizuo recalls Maoâ€™s Cultural Revolution (1966â€“76). The memory of its terror against â€œclass enemies,â€ committed in the name of cultural equality, leaves these thinkers allergic to progressive hyper-idealismâ€”the kind of idealism that believes egalitarian utopia would materialize if only critics and moderates did not stand in the way of historical progress. They recognize that thought pattern wherever it emerges, and they know that narrowmindedness, coercion, and worse come in its train. No more of that, please...

Indeed, the pseudo-Â­solidarity of identity politics further atomizes the individual by undermining the legitimacy of inherited cultures. This outcome is not accidental. Progressive liberals seek to weaken the hold of larger cultural collectives by erasing them from their accounts of the social world, accounts they disseminate using their dominance in the Westâ€™s humanities and social science departments. Many conservatives in the West criticize this project, and Chinese intellectuals find themselves in agreement."
